    <p class="therapy-story">I trained as a synchronised swimmer at national level. I know what it means to live inside a high-performance body — the discipline, the pain tolerance, the intimate knowledge of your own limits and how to push past them. I also know what it means when that body starts to fail you, when the gap between effort and recovery widens and doesn't close, when the injuries multiply and the fatigue becomes a kind of fog you can't train through.</p>
